```matlab
function [v,i] = taylor_exp(x,toll)
v = 0;
i = 0;
term = 1;
while term >= toll
    v = v+term;
    i = i+1;
    term = x^i/factorial(i);
end
```
The file name matches the function name. `v` accumulates the sum, `i` is the degree reached, `term = x^i/factorial(i)` is the next Taylor term; the while loop runs until a term drops below `toll`.

```matlab
x = 1;
tol = 1.0e-10;
[v,i] = taylor_exp(x,tol)
```
Capturing `[v,i]` returns both the polynomial value and the degree used.

```matlab
x = pi/4;
k = 1:50;
h = 2.^(-k);
r = (sin(x+h)-sin(x))./h;
```
`2.^(-k)` builds the 1x50 step vector; `./` divides each difference by its own `h`.

